				<td colspan="2"><span>Hello all. Im still very new to the game, been playing for about a month now. Im slowly learn some of the ins and outs. I've tryed my hand at almost every character (toon I think they are called) and I wanted to play a class that could farm plat and supplies pretty easy incase I desided to play another class (call me weird but I played Diablo 2 and had one of every class to keep it interesting), and I was told that Druid was the way to go so I started him up and lvled him to about 29 and I started watching more and more bards get in to groups faster and get as to more Ldon and found out that they can kite a whole lot more then 4 mobs. So here I am with a new bard that is now lvl 10 and still growing (im in the military and on duty so play time is slow this month). Arre there any Bards that I can hook up with and learn more about how to play this class on Morden Rasp (im a hands on guy more then a read and learn). I would also love to get into a guild if there are any recommendations on a good guild that excepts lower lvl toons.
<br />

<br />
Sorry about the long post. I didnt realize that it got this long.<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-4.gif" border="0" alt="Tongue out" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
Another thing, i have done the Newbie armor quest, what should i keep my eyes out for when it comes to armor and weapons and/or insturments.</span></td>
