			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Yet another Morden Rasp Newbie<a name="54660"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 1 04 1:04 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote"><b>Another thing, i have done the Newbie armor quest, what should i keep my eyes out for when it comes to armor and weapons and/or insturments.</b></span></blockquote>
<br />
For instruments, if you haven't already done it, run to the music store in Katta Castellum and get a Combine version of each instrument (lute, flute, horn, drum).  You can get a full set for less than 200p.
<br />

<br />
For weapons, I really don't have any suggestions there, other than check the stats on everything you see, and upgrade constantly.  One trick I use, though, is I keep <b><i>two</i></b> of each kind of weapon...one to actually melee with, and another to work on skillups.  What you're looking for in a skillup weapon is something with as low a delay as possible, most importantly, so that you can hit your target as often as possible while you practice.  Each swing of the weapon is another chance for a skill increase.  
<br />

<br />
Second,  you're looking for something with (strangely enough) low damage to go along with it.  The reason you want low damage is so you <b><i>don't</i></b> kill your practice mob as quickly.  The longer he stays alive, the longer you get to practice without searching for a new punching bag.  
<br />

<br />
I've suggested &quot;practice weapons&quot; to the devs more than once...weapons with a 0/10 damage/delay that would serve no other purpose than to allow you to do skillups.  If you had a weapon like that, you could even conceivably find one single light blue mob, drag him into an isolated corner and start beating on him, and you could go to sleep leaving your toon playing a heal song to hopefully cover any damage the mob lands.  Then, just return the next morning, switch weapons and finish off your &quot;sparring partner,&quot; and you have your melee skill maxed, just like people do with their instrument skills (which is probably why the devs haven't put them in the game. *grin*).</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%"><a href="http://tinyurl.com/3re4w"target="_blank">Elfiz Koshtello</a><br>
